+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EWqFPYL1jvA3ZYfEmTcsnb","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've thoroughly explored the entire codebase. Here's a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Project Overview\n\nThis is a **Full-Text Search Feature** for an Express + SQLite note-taking API. The task is to add SQLite FTS5 (Full-Text Search) capabilities to an existing CRUD API.\n\n**Project**: `bench-fts-search` v1.0.0\n\n---\n\n## Complete File Contents\n\n### 1. **package.json**\nLocated at `/workspace/package.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-fts-search\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Full-text search feature benchmark\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/ tests/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\",\n    \"seed\": \"tsx src/seed.ts\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"better-sqlite3\": \"^11.0.0\",\n    \"express\": \"^4.21.0\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.0\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.0.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.56.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@types/better-sqlite3\": \"^7.6.0\",\n    \"@types/express\": \"^4.17.0\",\n    \"supertest\": \"^7.0.0\",\n    \"@types/supertest\": \"^6.0.0\",\n    \"tsx\": \"^4.0.0\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key Scripts:**\n- `build`: Compile TypeScript\n- `lint`: Run ESLint\n- `test`: Run tests with Vitest\n- `seed`: Seed database with sample notes\n\n---\n\n### 2. **src/db.ts**\nLocated at `/workspace/src/db.ts`\n\nCreates and seeds the SQLite database with a `notes` table. Contains:\n- `createDatabase(path?)`: Creates SQLite DB with WAL mode and foreign keys enabled\n- `seedDatabase(db)`: Populates DB with 45 sample notes about various topics\n- `getSeedNotes()`: Returns sample notes with titles, bodies, and JSON tags\n\nThe notes table structure:\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS notes (\n  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n  title TEXT NOT NULL,\n  body TEXT NOT NULL,\n  tags TEXT DEFAULT '[]',\n  created_at TEXT DEFAULT (datetime('now')),\n  updated_at TEXT DEFAULT (datetime('now'))\n)\n```\n\nSample seed data includes notes about programming, cooking, travel, music, science, and more.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **src/models.ts**\nLocated at `/workspace/src/models.ts`\n\nTypeScript interfaces for type safety:\n\n```typescript\nexport interface Note {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  body: string;\n  tags: string; // JSON array as string\n  created_at: string;\n  updated_at: string;\n}\n\nexport interface NoteInput {\n  title: string;\n  body: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n}\n\nexport interface SearchResult {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n  snippet: string;\n  rank: number;\n}\n\nexport interface SuggestResult {\n  id: number;\n  title: string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **src/routes.ts**\nLocated at `/workspace/src/routes.ts`\n\nExpress Router with CRUD endpoints:\n\n**Implemented Endpoints:**\n- `GET /notes` - List all notes (with optional `?tag=X` filter)\n- `GET /notes/:id` - Get single note by ID\n- `POST /notes` - Create note (validates title & body required)\n- `PUT /notes/:id` - Update note (partial updates supported)\n- `DELETE /notes/:id` - Delete note\n\nAll routes include error handling through next(err).\n\n---\n\n### 5. **src/errors.ts**\nLocated at `/workspace/src/errors.ts`\n\nCustom error classes and middleware:\n\n```typescript\nclass NotFoundError (extends Error, statusCode: 404)\nclass ValidationError (extends Error, statusCode: 400)\nfunction errorHandler() // Express error middleware\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. **src/server.ts**\nLocated at `/workspace/src/server.ts`\n\nExpress app factory functions:\n\n```typescript\nexport function createApp(dbPath?: string): App\nexport function createSeededApp(dbPath?: string): App\n```\n\n- Creates Express app with JSON middleware\n- Attaches routes and error handler\n- Can optionally seed database\n- Auto-starts server on port 3000 if run directly\n\n---\n\n### 7. **src/seed.ts**\nLocated at `/workspace/src/seed.ts`\n\nCommand-line script to populate database:\n- Takes optional dbPath argument (default: `notes.db`)\n- Seeds database and logs count of inserted notes\n- Closes DB connection after completion\n\n---\n\n### 8. **tests/notes.test.ts**\nLocated at `/workspace/tests/notes.test.ts`\n\n15 CRUD tests (must continue passing):\n\n1. GET /notes returns all notes\n2. GET /notes/:id returns specific note\n3. GET /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n4. POST /notes creates note with title and body\n5. POST /notes creates note with tags\n6. POST /notes returns 400 without title\n7. POST /notes returns 400 without body\n8. PUT /notes/:id updates note\n9. PUT /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n10. DELETE /notes/:id removes note\n11. DELETE /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n12. GET /notes?tag=X filters by tag\n13. Notes have created_at timestamp\n14. Notes have updated_at timestamp\n15. PUT updates updated_at timestamp\n\nUses Vitest + Supertest for HTTP testing.\n\n---\n\n### 9. **tests/search.test.ts**\nLocated at `/workspace/tests/search.test.ts`\n\n20 Search-specific tests (must pass after implementation):\n\n**Search Tests (1-12):**\n1. GET /notes/search?q=keyword returns matching notes\n2. Results have snippet field\n3. Snippets contain `<mark>` tags around matched terms\n4. Results ranked by relevance (most relevant first)\n5. Exact phrase matching with quotes\n6. Results include id, title, snippet, rank fields\n7. Nonexistent query returns empty array\n8. Missing q parameter returns 400\n9. Empty q parameter returns 400\n10. Pagination: page=1 returns first 20 results\n11. Pagination: page=2 returns next results\n12. Pagination response includes total count\n\n**Suggest Tests (13-15):**\n13. GET /notes/search/suggest?q=prefix returns up to 5 titles\n14. Suggest results match prefix in title\n15. Missing q parameter returns 400\n\n**FTS Sync Tests (16-18):**\n16. FTS syncs on create - new note appears in search\n17. FTS syncs on update - updated content appears in search\n18. FTS syncs on delete - deleted note disappears from search\n\n**Additional Tests (19-20):**\n19. Special characters in query don't crash\n20. Search response time under 100ms for seeded dataset\n\n---\n\n### 10. **TASK.md**\nLocated at `/workspace/TASK.md`\n\nComplete task specification:\n\n**Requirements Summary:**\n1. **Search Endpoint** (`GET /notes/search?q=<query>`)\n   - Full-text search using SQLite FTS5\n   - BM25 ranking\n   - Snippet highlighting with `<mark>` tags\n   - Quoted phrase support\n   - Pagination (20 per page, `?page=N` parameter)\n   - Returns `{ results: SearchResult[], total: number, page: number, perPage: number }`\n   - Returns 400 if q missing/empty\n\n2. **Suggest Endpoint** (`GET /notes/search/suggest?q=<prefix>`)\n   - Autocomplete returning up to 5 titles\n   - Prefix matching against content\n   - Returns `{ results: SuggestResult[] }`\n   - Returns 400 if q missing/empty\n\n3. **FTS Index Synchronization**\n   - Keep FTS in sync on create, update, delete\n   - Use SQLite triggers or manual sync\n\n**Validation:**\n- All 35 tests (15 existing + 20 new) must pass\n- Run with `npm test`\n\n---\n\n## Project Structure Summary\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── package.json              # Dependencies and scripts\n├── tsconfig.json            # TypeScript config\n├── vitest.config.ts         # Vitest config\n├── TASK.md                  # Complete requirements\n├── src/\n│   ├── db.ts               # Database setup & seeding\n│   ├── models.ts           # TypeScript interfaces\n│   ├── routes.ts           # CRUD endpoints (existing)\n│   ├── errors.ts           # Error classes\n│   ├── server.ts           # Express app factory\n│   └── seed.ts             # Seeding script\n└── tests/\n    ├── notes.test.ts       # 15 CRUD tests\n    └── search.test.ts      # 20 search tests\n```\n\n---\n\n## What Needs to be Implemented\n\nBased on the test requirements, you need to implement:\n\n1. **FTS5 Virtual Table** - Create and maintain an FTS5 index for note titles and bodies\n2. **Search Endpoint** - `/notes/search?q=...` with ranking and snippets\n3. **Suggest Endpoint** - `/notes/search/suggest?q=...` for autocomplete\n4. **Sync Mechanism** - Keep FTS index in sync with CRUD operations\n\nAll code is written in **TypeScript (ESM module format)** and tested with **Vitest + Supertest**."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a0baf56 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 30861\ntool_uses: 11\nduration_ms: 21860</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc061532-d8b4-439f-9fcc-57aab60f7c4d","uuid":"b78acd25-ca9f-446c-b659-c52bb9c03662","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase thoroughly. I need to understand:\n1. The overall project structure (all files)\n2. The contents of src/db.ts, src/models.ts, src/routes.ts, src/errors.ts, src/server.ts, src/seed.ts\n3. The test files tests/notes.test.ts and tests/search.test.ts\n4. package.json for dependencies and scripts\n\nRead ALL of these files completely and provide their full contents.","agentId":"a0baf56","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've thoroughly explored the entire codebase. Here's a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Project Overview\n\nThis is a **Full-Text Search Feature** for an Express + SQLite note-taking API. The task is to add SQLite FTS5 (Full-Text Search) capabilities to an existing CRUD API.\n\n**Project**: `bench-fts-search` v1.0.0\n\n---\n\n## Complete File Contents\n\n### 1. **package.json**\nLocated at `/workspace/package.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-fts-search\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"Full-text search feature benchmark\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/ tests/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\",\n    \"seed\": \"tsx src/se